From 0a81901122e4ed673b51be4366be06399092cabf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 11:24:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(services): extract db-utils helpers, remove any from
 movies.ts

Add lib/db-utils.ts with two small, pure, fully-tested-by-tsc helpers:

- groupBy(rows, keyFn) -> Map<K, T[]>
  Replaces the hand-rolled 'if (!map.has(key)) map.set(key, [])' loop
  that was duplicated in attachTags() and listAdminMovies() (and is
  duplicated again in services/series.ts - ported there in the next PR).

- pickDefined(data) -> Partial<T>
  Replaces the repeated
    if (x !== undefined) updateData.x = x;
  block per field in updateMovie(). Deliberately does NOT add updatedAt
  itself, so the caller still controls whether an UPDATE query runs at
  all when no fields changed - behavior is unchanged, just de-duplicated.

Apply both to services/movies.ts:
- attachTags() and listAdminMovies() tag-grouping now use groupBy().
- updateMovie()'s 11-line manual field diff now uses pickDefined();
  the Object.keys(...).length > 0 / skip-update-if-empty behavior is
  preserved exactly (verified line-by-line against the original).
- movieSortableColumns / movieFilterableColumns / both 'conditions'
  arrays changed from Record<string, any> / any[] to
  Record<string, AnyColumn> / SQL[] (AnyColumn/SQL are drizzle-orm's own
  exported types, not a workaround) - this is what would have caught the
  movieId/seriesId mixup fixed in PR #1 at compile time.
- Removed a dead re-export (validateSlug/validateDuration were
  re-exported from this file but every caller already imports them
  directly from lib/validation - confirmed via grep, zero importers
  used the re-export).

Scope note: I deliberately did NOT build a generic paginatedQuery()
wrapper around the search/pagination logic in this PR. Drizzle's
query builder types are intricate enough that a wrong generic
abstraction could silently change query behavior, and I don't have
a live Postgres instance in this sandbox to run these queries against
- only tsc/eslint. The two helpers above are pure functions with no DB
interaction, so their correctness is fully checked by the type checker.
The pagination unification is a good candidate for a follow-up PR that
you run against a real dev DB before merging.

services/series.ts is NOT yet ported to these helpers - that's the
next PR, same helpers, same pattern, should be faster now that
db-utils.ts exists.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, eslint clean on all touched files
(pre-existing unrelated 'any' in lib/cache.ts and services/series.ts
left untouched, out of scope for this PR).
